value.name: Cerro de Punta - Wikipedia
value.snippet: It is located at coordinates 18.172458 and -66.591839W. The nearest populated place to Cerro de Punta is Urbanización Vega Linda, located 3.3 miles (5.3 km) away. Geology. Unlike many Caribbean mountains, Cerro de Punta is not a volcano but simply the highest point in the Cordillera Central.

value.name: Cerro Punta Loop | Map, Guide - Chiriquí, Panama | AllTrails
value.snippet: Description This is a great trail for a morning hike. It's short yet very steep and strenuous, with awesome views of the Cerro Punta Valley, Volcan, and the Talamanca Range. Follow the trail clockwise starting on the Entre Rios road. Park the car on the edge of the road. You can also take a public bus and get off at the Entre Rios junction.

value.name: Cerro de Punta | Discover Puerto Rico
value.snippet: Cerro Punta in Jayuya is the island's highest peak at an elevation of 1,338 meters above sea level. Get panoramic views of the island by either driving or hiking up the mountain. If you're driving up, it's recommended to do so in a four-wheel drive. The hike up the road that leads to the peak is about 30 minutes long.

value.name: Cerro Punta, Chiriquí - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Cerro Punta is a city and corregimiento in Tierras Altas District, Chiriquí Province, Panama. [1] [2] Cerro Punta is located in Panama's western highlands at an altitude of 6,500 feet (2,000 metres), just south of the Continental Divide. Many of the inhabitants of the village and the surrounding areas are indigenous Native Americans.
